  "prompt": "How do I use the desktop version of Instagram?",
  "response": "To use the desktop version of Instagram, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open a web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, etc.)\n\n2. Go to www.instagram.com\n\n3. Click \"Log In\" in the top right corner\n\n4. Enter your username and password\n\n5. You can now:\n- View your feed\n- Like and comment on posts\n- View stories\n- Search for accounts\n- View profiles\n\nImportant notes:\n- You cannot create new posts directly from desktop\n- You can upload photos/videos through a workaround on Chrome\n- Some features are limited compared to mobile app\n- Best for browsing and exploring content\n- For full functionality, use mobile app\n\nIf you want more features, you can download Instagram desktop apps like:\n- Ramme (Windows/Mac)\n- Gram (Windows)\n- Electron Instagram (cross-platform)\n\nThese third-party apps might offer additional desktop functionality.",
